{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 62,
  "title": "第六十二章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "道者萬物之奧。"
    },
    {
      "text": "善人之寶，"
    },
    {
      "text": "不善人之所保。"
    },
    {
      "text": "美言可以市，尊行可以加人。"
    },
    {
      "text": "人之不善，何棄之有？"
    },
    {
      "text": "故立天子，置三公，"
    },
    {
      "text": "雖有拱璧以先駟馬，不如坐進此道。"
    },
    {
      "text": "古之所以貴此道者何？不曰以求得，有罪以免邪？故為天下貴。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "奧，猶曖也。可得庇蔭之辭。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "寶以為用也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "保以全也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言道無所不先，物無有貴於此也。雖有珍寶璧馬，無以匹之，美言之則可以奪眾貨之賈，故曰，美言可以市也，尊行之則千里之外應之，故曰，可以加於人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不善當保道以免放。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 9
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "言以尊行道也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 16
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "此道，上之所云也。言故立天子、置三公，尊其位、重其人，所以為道也。物無有貴於此者。故雖有拱抱寶璧以先，駟馬而進之，不如坐而進此道也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 28
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以求則得求，以免則得免，無所而不施，故為天下貴也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
